            <h2 align="center">Scenic Spot Introduction</h2>
            <table align="center" width="90%">
                <tr>
                    <td><b>Old Beijing the imperial palace, the Forbidden City, is China's twenty-four emperors of the Ming and qing dynasties imperial palace, now refers to the national Palace Museum in Beijing, is located in the centre of Beijing, is incomparable ancient architecture masterpiece, is also the world's largest and most complete existing the ancient wooden structure buildings. Palace buildings are wooden structure, yellow glazed tile roof, blue and white stone base, decorated with golden and brilliant color paintings. The building is arranged along a north-south axis and spread out on both sides. According to its layout and function, it is divided into two major parts: the outer court and the inner court. The architectural atmosphere of the outer and inner court is quite different. The outer court was centered on the three main halls of the hall of supreme harmony, the hall of central harmony and the hall of bao he. In addition, there are two wings of the east wenhua temple, wenyuan pavilion, upper cs courtyard, south three; In the west, there are such buildings as the hall of martial arts and the house of ministers. The architecture is magnificent, the courtyard is clear and open, symbolizing the supremacy of the feudal regime. The inner court centers on the three palaces of ganqing palace, jiaotaidian palace and kunning palace, with the two wings of yangxin palace, east six palace, west six palace, fast palace and yuqing palace. It was the residence of feudal emperors and their wives.</b></td>
